Last Session of Nepal 's Parliament Set for January
KATHMANDU , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- Nepali King Birendra has called the 15th session of parliament , the last for the present parliament , for January 13 , 1999 , the king 's Principal Press Secretariat said in a notice Monday .
The major function of the session , usually for passage of bills , will be to take the confidence vote on the new tri-partite government led by Girija Prasad Koirala , parliamentary sources said .
The sources said that after the voting , the parliament elected in the mid-term polls in November 1994 is expected to be dissolved for general elections by mid-April 1999 .
The 11-member cabinet comprising the Nepali Congress , the Communist Party of Nepal ( United Marxism-Leninism , CPN-UML ) and the Nepal Sadbhavana Party was formed with the objective of conducting free , fair and impartial elections .
The 10 ministers appointed last Friday were sworn in Monday .
Under the country 's Constitution , a new government must obtain the vote of confidence in the Lower House of Parliament within 30 days of its formation .
